   BASIC COMMANDS:
1: GENERAL
git --version                                          :check installed git version
git init                                               :create empty git repositry
git status                                             :check working directory & staging area status
git log                                                :display all commits of current branch

2:COMMIT CREATION & ACCESS
git ls-files                                           :list data in stagging area
git add filename
git add .                                              :Add single file or all WD files to staging area
git commit -m "message"
git checkout commitid                                  :checkout commit(detached head)

3:BRANCH CREATION AND ACCESS
git branch branch_name                                 :git switch branch_name: create new branch
git checkout                                           :go to branch
git checkout -b branch_name  git switch -c branch_name :craate and access new branch
git merge other_branch                                 :bring other_branchs change to current branch

3:DELETING DATA 
WD FILE*            git rm filename                     :run command after file was deleted from working directory
Unstagedchanges     git checkout (--) .
                    git restore filename or .           :revert changes in tracked file
                    git clean -df                       : delete untracked files
Staged changes      git reset filename &
                    git checkout --filename             :Remove files from stagging area
                    git restore --Staged filename or .
latest commits(s)   git reset HEAD~1
                    git reset --soft HEAD~1             :undo latest(~1) commits
                    git reset --hard HEAD~1
Branches            git branch -D branch_name           :delete branch



